  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a large clay or ceramic tagine over medium heat.",
    "Add sliced ginger and cook for 2 minutes, until fragrant.",
    "Add minced garlic and cook for an additional minute, until softened.",
    "Add fennel seeds, turmeric, coriander seeds, and mustard seeds. Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add snapper fillets and cook for 2 minutes on each side, until browned.",
    "Add fermented sauerkraut, white wine, chicken broth, salt, and black pepper. Stir to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 8-10 minutes, or until the fish is cooked through.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with fresh parsley or dill, if desired."
  ],
